reviewText: This Collectors' Edition is excellent value for money - you get both Janet's Velvet Rope and All For You tours.High energy, tight choreography and exuberant performances make repeated viewings. From the two concerts, there are recurrent themes of:1) Janet performing her Control medley of hits and an acoustic set of Let's Wait Awhile type ballads.2) Janet selecting a male audience member and proceed to do a sexy routine on him, though it's far raunchier on the Live In Hawaii show.3) There's a very vivid, colourful and lively circus/funfair/court jester part.4) With all that jumping, Janet does ask the audience to help her out to sing parts of the songs but I'm thankful this isn't overdone.5) A segment where Janet and the dancers don masks.6) Closing songs for both shows is Together Again - very fun and memorable, great finale.On Live In Hawaii, there are some extras. A Janet interview and clips of her doing her stuff with several selected  men from the audience. What a tease!

reviewText: How often do artists release a two-concert DVD set deal? Not often. If you are a fan of Janet, nab this one. It's an excellent deal; the price is unbelievably cheap for a combo like this. The concerts themselves are just classic Janet, i highly recommend this!
